    "body": "### Problem\n\nDouble action from Enter, Backspace, and Tab keys both in all modes in a file buffer.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Open any file in nvim 0.12\n2. Press Enter, Backspace, or Tab\n3. Observe the action occurs twice\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n Enter, Backspace, and Tab keys should only trigger one action.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.0 fc7e5cf\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\ndon't have vim\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nubuntu 24.04.4 LTS\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.13.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nvia tarball and symlinking it to /usr/local/bin/nvim",
